import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['income'], data['health'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Income')
    ax.set_ylabel('Health')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between income and health?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    population_by_region = data.groupby('region')['population'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.bar(population_by_region['region'], population_by_region['population'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different regions?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('region')['income'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['region'], data['income'])
    plt.title('What is the average income by region?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
